 * New FastAcyclicNetwork class and supporting changes/refactoring.
 * A number of problem domains have been switched to using the new
acyclic network where appropriate, e.g. binary logic domains such as
logical-XOR and binary multiplexer.

This is the last major step in implementing feedforward-only (acyclic)
networks. I've ironed out a few bugs just now and run the code with
debug asserts switched on, so I have a reasonable confidence it's
working as expected, but I'll need to run some more extensive tests to
be sure.

There have been a number of other lesser submissions recently so check
the SVN log for more info there.

SVN URL is:
https://sharpneat.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/sharpneat/trunk/SharpNeatV2

  --Colin.
